The '''Joule Centre''' is a research centre based at the [[University of Manchester]], England, that researches energy.
==History== The Joule Centre for Energy Research was founded in October 2005 with £5 million from the [[Northwest Regional Development Agency]] and it cost £10 million.
==Structure== It is based at the [[University of Manchester]].
==Function== It conducts energy research.
